      "info.s4.li5": "Paste that URL in Options: the transcription one in <em>“Transcription Gem URL”</em>, the message one in <em>“Contributor message Gem URL”</em>.",
      "info.s4.gem1h": "Transcription Gem (Song → Gem)",
      "info.s4.gem1p": "Receives the YouTube link (and duration) and returns the transcription. The <strong>Gem lyrics review</strong> button uses this same Gem: it pastes the Transcript lyrics instead of the link and copies the corrected answer to your clipboard.",
      "info.s4.gem2h": "Contributor message Gem (Diffgenie)",
      "info.s4.gem2p": "Receives the original lyrics, the corrected ones and the contributor data, and writes the message.",
      "info.s5.h": "5. Highlighter",
      "info.s5.p1": "Works only on Musixmatch. In the popup's “Highlighter” tab:",
      "info.s5.li1": "Create <strong>lists</strong> with a name, a color and (optionally) a keyboard shortcut.",
      "info.s5.li2": "Select text on the page and apply a list: with its shortcut, or with that list's <em>“Apply”</em> button in the popup. All occurrences of the phrase get highlighted and persist across reloads.",
      "info.s5.li3": "<strong>Auto-mark opened songs:</strong> marks in the task list the songs you already opened, so you don't enter them again. Configurable: “on open” or “on open without completing”.",
      "info.s5.li4": "<strong>New:</strong> the mark color is configurable (pastel green by default) and you can mark/unmark any song by hand with a <strong>single right-click</strong> on its card — the browser's context menu still appears; the ⋯ button stays reserved.",
      "info.s5.note": "Note: the highlighter works on normal page text (titles, guides, data); it can't paint inside the editable lyrics field (it's a text box).",
      "info.s6.h": "6. Entrance animations",
      "info.s6.p1": "In <strong>Advanced options → Advanced</strong> you can pick an entrance animation for the floating buttons (30 available: meteor shower, pinball, domino, Big Bang, popcorn…). The default is <strong>Random</strong>, which changes on every task without repeating the previous one. “None” disables them. On leaving the editor there's always the same exit animation (they hide to the right).",
      "info.s7.h": "7. Backup (Export / Import)",
      "info.s7.p1": "In <strong>Advanced options</strong> you can <em>export</em> all your settings (shortcuts, buttons, highlighter lists, Gems, etc.) to a <code>.json</code> file and <em>import</em> it back anytime or on another computer.",
      "info.s8.h": "8. Per-OS notes",
